metadata.name: Plottable Thousands #71
metadata.description:
'Thousands' explores the packing of recursive circles and golden angle spirals distributing various particles on a A4 canvas.

A SVG file can be exported (right click save) to plot the piece physically.

You can enjoy the digital version that simulate ink effects and optional, thanks to the utility token decoupling, get a physical one: the digital NFT is the recipe to a plottable art piece, owning it confers the right to plot or request a physical plot from @greweb (https://greweb.me/plots/nft). @greweb would use fountain pens but other plotting artists are free to achieve it with their own materials and ship to collectors – as long as NFT is owned at request time.

Code: https://github.com/gre/gre/tree/master/doodles/plottable-thousands

@greweb – 2022 – tech: WebGL + Rust + WASM – CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

metadata.name: The Space Inside #86
metadata.description:
Points fill in shapes on a warped noise field. The resulting images range from soft water colors to distorted, pixelated CRT screens. 

The image is drawn at 3000x3000px and scaled to the browser size. 

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 3000x3000px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

Features:
- Two palette sets
- Light or dark background
- 70% color image, 30% monochrome
- Various combinations of circles and rectangles
- All rectangles 
- 7 types of shapes: random circles, packed circles, checkerboard, orbs, ring, spiral, checkerboard and orbs
- Rectangles snap to a grid
- Fuzzy lines connected groups of drawing points
- Fuzzy lines around the dots
- Bright border on the shapes

Rare
- 9% to have a soft monochrome and color palette

metadata.name: Mount Doodle #478
metadata.description:
Tried my best to make every doodle aesthetically pleasing to the eyes.
However, just like nature, beauty often lies in imperfections. :)

Made with p5.js.
Primary split 5% with The Processing Foundation.

Keys
- 1: view 1000px png (Default)
- 2: download 2000px png
- 4: download 4000px png
- 8: download 8000px png
- s: save the image as PNG

When downloading higher resolution pngs, it might take several seconds to redraw the whole image. Download will start immediately after redrawing is completed. Please bear with the slow rendering.

metadata.name: Over the Air #340
metadata.description:
During the last couple of decades, over the air television signals and antennas switched to digital, bringing with them a new form of static and distortion as the signal is broken up. "Over the Air" is inspired by these digital distortions, incorporating aspects of them into the same grid-like structure seen on the television. Additional patterns are combined in the grid with these distortions to create the final artwork.

Patterns for the individual blocks in the grid are divided into categories, and various amounts are picked for each work, with dozens of possible mixtures. Patterns can flow in different directions across the varied canvases. Distribution of these patterns across the grid varies from work to work, providing for different feels as they bunch together or spread apart.

metadata.name: Elementary Cellular Emoji Automata #292
metadata.description:
Features the full set of 1761 emojis, including skin tone and gender modifiers and all flags.
Arranged using the full 256 ruleset of one-dimensional cellular automata

If “random seed” is true then the seed of the generation is randomized using Math.random() meaning that the pattern will change on regeneration.
The ruleset, emoji, colors and all other properties will remain the same.

Auto-adjusts to screen size

Compatible with as many browsers and systems as possible

metadata.name: WTBS Logo with Friends #136
metadata.description:
Did you know that WTBS is now sixth months old? If we were Will’s baby, we’d be sitting up and prepping to crawl — the literal baby steps that precede an entire lifetime of movement. 

Play is another integral part of our development. Play teaches us to connect, laugh, share, love, and learn. It helps form our earliest friendships that mold us into who we are destined to become. Over the last six months we have had the immense pleasure of forming new relationships with some of the amazing artists that comprise of the fxhash community. 

It is the love and support of new friends Laurent Houdard, Ada Ada Ada, elsif, and Camille Roux that made our first (official) collaboration possible. Thank you so much for the idea, the vision, the art, the time, and the wrangling to make this possible. 

Each letter is imbued with the unique style of an artist, based on a framework created by Laurent. There is a small chance of receiving a piece with two of the same style, with the rarest possibility of receiving one with all four quadrants the same. 

Collect with love and the knowledge that your support means the world to us. Thank you for listening every week, and for the messages and stories that you share with us. We can’t wait to continue to grow.

Thank you so much again to Laurent, Ada, elsif, and Camille. This is what community is.

metadata.name: Pobbles #250
metadata.description:
The pobbles are generative blob-rocks: staring in silence, sometimes half-smiling, generally bored. 

• The pobbles are digital recreations of a series of rock-doodles by S.F.Kislev (my big brother). They are an attempt to capture a specific, singular handwriting, and evolve it using code. 
• See the original, 2014 handmade version here - https://pobbles.tez.page..
• Alternative titles considered include Peggles™, Plops™, Blobbies™, Floofs™, Flintstones™, Lardies™, Plumps™, Fats™ and Wet-Ones™. 
• The pobbles are written entirely in paper.js and p5.js. 
• The pobbles are an effort to take generative art into the realm of the cute. 
• They work well with toddlers.

🖨️ Collectors minting at the first auction tier receive a hand-crafted riso print of their pobble. Color variation between the file and the print will apply. 🖨️

metadata.name: In the Edge #14
metadata.description:
./ In the Edge

It's been a long time since your journey began, caring for the ones you love, pursuing your dreams, and giving the best of you. 

Now you know you can't go back, you can't go further, you know your time is coming.

How far did you go? It doesn't matter, you did it right. Your accomplishments will serve well the next generations in their journeys, in their search for themselves.

Now it's time to stop, time to take a moment and contemplate the vast universe.

Soon all of this will be ending.

You did it right.

Embrace the void.
=========
=========


./ Color scheme (feature)
There are 12 color schemes and with each set, specific arrays for color collections for the space, stars, planet, and accent colors. 

These are color schemes in the known universe of "In the Edge":
- Mars visions
- Cyberpunk
- Unknown passenger 
- Renegade
- Primary
- Coral
- r.e.d.
- Machines of an ancient-future 
- The void
- Tinted light 
- Malibu dreams
- Atari (horrendous brown, red and yellowish combinations... I love it)

./ Mountain type (feature)
In the Edge, you will find a mountain, and that mountain will be special, which type will you find?

- Parallela insolitum
- Sandy dunes of the truth
- Wavy uncertainty
- Intrinsic soul ridges
- Cerritulus formationis

./ Mountain direction (feature)
Life is about direction... mountains too.

- Left
- Right
- Left-Right

./ Space scenery
This is the spicy touch, some of the iterations will have animation and others will not, giving you a clear view of the magnificent space in front of you.

- Clean (NOT animated)
- Windy planet (animated)
- Topographic planet (animated)
- Meteor shower (animated)

./ Distance from Earth (feature)
How far did you go? Your travel could be from 1 lightyear to 999,999,999 lightyears (that's a lot of lights and years!). However just a few will pass the barrier of 99,999,999ly.

// Additional perks
./ Planet names 
Planet names are unique and they are conformed by three blocks.

The first block is a conjunction between ancient Latin names and Japanese last names. 

The second block takes the last three characters from the fxhash.

The third block takes three numbers from the number seed obtained from fxrand().

The planet you land will be unique, as unique as you are.

// Controls
./ Pause-Play animation
Because maybe (and just maybe) you want to freeze the perfect moment before closing your eyes.

[Backspace] Pause.
[Enter] Play

Applies to "Space scenery" features windy planet, topographic planet, and meteor shower.
